{Which is the best way to ensure the central pawns' safety?} 19... Bb5 $1 {
Black has to exchange the minor pieces in order to prevent c5 from becoming
weak.} ({The game went} 19... a4 $6 20. Rfd1 Qd6 21. Rd2 $1 Be6 22. h3 Rc7 23.
Nf4 {Threatening Nxd5 followed by Rcd1 but also Nd3.} c4 24. Qxd6 Rxd6 25. Ne2
$14 {with pleasant control on the dark squares, Petrosian, T-Spassky, B Moscow
1966 (½-½, 50)}) 20. Rfe1 Bxe2 21. Rxe2 d4 22. Rce1 Re6 $1 23. Qxa5 c4 {
The hanging pawns have reached the fourth rank, offering Black excellent
compensation for the lost pawn.} *

