{With his last move, White has occupied the central square. What springs up to
mind is the weird knight's placement on the edge. Black to move.} 18... Nc6 $1
$17 {Immediately starting the fight against the blockade while also returning
the knight into play. But as logical as this sounds, there is a small tactical
detail that Black had to foresee.} 19. Nxc6 $6 Bxc6 {Black has a dream
position, but the next move just loses material.} 20. Bxc4 $2 Qa5 $1 $19 21.
Bb3 Bxa4 22. Bxa4 Rec8 23. Bc6 (23. b4 Qa6 24. Qb3 Rc3 25. b5 Qa5 $19) 23...
Qa6 24. Rc1 Bxb2 {0-1 Grigorian,K (2465) -Geller,E (2590) Leningrad 1977} *

