{In the absence of a clear plan in the centre, White has tried to build up
some kingside pressure. Is this plan sound?} 24... g6 $1 {This strong move
forces the queen to embark on dangerous trajectories.} 25. Qxh6 (25. Qg4 h5 26.
Qh3 b5 27. a3 Rce7 $17 {followed by ...Qb6 leaves the white queen awfully
placed.}) 25... Bg7 26. Qe3 Nxd4 27. Qd3 Nxf3+ 28. Qxf3 d4 29. Qg4 Qa8 {
Attacking the knight and threatening ...Bf3.} 30. Rxd4 (30. Ne2 Bf3 31. Qf4
Rce7 $19 {also wins material}) 30... Bf3 31. Qf4 Be5 32. Qg5 Bxd4 33. Rxd4 Rc5
$17 {and Black converted his extra exchange in Malisauskas,V (2525) -Van der
Sterren,P (2510) Yerevan 1996 (0-1, 54)} *

