{This is a position with mutual pins, piece tension and small tactical details.
Can Black settle things to his favour?} 17... Qxf3 $1 {Now and the next move
are forced, yielding Black a win while the alternatives would lose due to
White's material advantage and due to the permanent threat of b6-b7.} 18. b7
Rd7 $1 {Unpinning the bishop while keeping it defended. Black wins as the rook
on h1 is also hanging.} 19. bxa8=Q {Otherwise ...Bxb7.} Bxa8 20. Qa4 Rxd1+ 21.
